title: Experiment: This Is What It Sounds Like When You Put Bass Strings on a Guitar | Music News @ Ultimate-Guitar.Com
text:
UG News editor since early 2013. King Crimson fan. I handle the news around here. Posted 43 minutes ago 5 
Mr. Davie504 from YouTube offered another one of his experiments, this time around putting a set of bass strings on a regular six-string electric guitar. 
The musician pointed out that only the top four strings are bass strings (so E, A, D and G), while the bottom two (B and high E) are regular guitar strings. 
You can check out the clip in the embedded player below.
